      • leave

        protected void leave(Message message,
                     java.lang.String sessionName,
                     char objectType,
                     java.lang.String clientName)
        leave the client of this name has left the managed object. Remove the client connection, and inform all observers of this change. If we have an incoming message, than send a reply message back to the proxy side.
        Parameters:
        message - the message being processed or null. If this parameter is null, this means that we had a client leave a Session (either deliberately or the result of a lost connection), and we are tidying up it's session, channel and token connections.
        sessionName - the current session name.
        objectType - the type of object this client is leaving.
        clientName - the name of the client leaving this managed object.
